From earlier tastes I still value inventive multitrack vocal overdubs that color without burying, tight bass/drums and a warm, dense low end, midrange punch and guitar‑forward weight, economical song‑serving solos, preserved attack/transient punch and micro‑dynamics, and tactile analogue bite.
I dislike piano/organ‑heavy or horn‑forward mixes that dilute rock immediacy; close, breathy singer‑only presentations; over‑slick or hyper‑bright masters; remasters that flatten dynamics; syrupy, cozy treatments; and loose, unfocused compilations that blur into sameness.

